body:
I think it would be cool if Riot made it to where giant characters had footstep sound effects added in for them that could be toggled on and off like shadows. I think it would make you feel a ton more powerful/important if your giant character had really big and heavy sounding footsteps when they were running down a lane to initiate a fight. Characters this could apply for are: {{champion:12}} {{champion:53}} {{champion:31}} {{champion:3}} {{champion:150}} {{champion:120}} {{champion:54}} {{champion:57}} {{champion:111}} {{champion:421}} {{champion:14}} {{champion:48}} {{champion:106}} {{champion:154}} 
Maybe {{champion:75}} and {{champion:58}} while they have their ultimate abilities active as well to make them extra intimidating in a fight.

I just feel like something like this would help with someone playing these champs feel more powerful while playing. Sion already has something like it on his ultimate, why not have it as a feature for others? Besides, how much does it take to record footsteps that match-up with each champions walk cycle? Just speed up the footsteps with the same percentage multiplier as their movement speed increase.
